		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> DCON 2002 Let the fights Begin<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.93)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5383'>Mike "The Judge" Blumberg</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=5383&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> July 24, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Deciphercon 2002 Issue- Based on the popularity of last years article and the amount of trash talking going around, 2002 DCON might be worse.<br>
<br>
The Matchups: <br>
<br>
Clint Hayes VS. John Patch Patchell <br>
<br>
Clint called patch out on the buzzboard, calling him a douchebag and other various descriptive terms and patchell wanted revenge. As soon as he paid his entrance fee, he saw Clint off to the side of the room and broke into a full gallop towards him. Clint was discussing the finer points of the latest wwe pay-per-view with Adam Drake when Drake saw the on-charging Patchell. Drake pushed Clint out of the way and Adams elbow met patchells forehead at about 40 mph. Patchells forehead split open about an inch and got blood all over Adams favorite Lita t-shirt. Adam, much to his surprise had pushed Clint into the table where Enrique Huerta was doing deck checks. Enrique had a triple espresso from starbucks on the table and spilled it all over the deck he was checking. Turns out it was some extra large black man named Roofus who had just begun playing Lord of the Rings and was standing near by as Enrique was informing him that he couldnt have 16 companions in his deck. Roofus in a fit of rage picked up clint by his belt loop and flung him into a cement wall. Clint is recovering nicely in the hotels lobby with an icepack on his head and may be able to play day 1. <br>
<br>
Matchup #2 <br>
<br>
Munchkin  VS Some loser from Huntsville<br>
<br>
Munchkin came to DCON wearing a little short skirt and a very lowcut top and 6 inch platforms. Some redneck loser from Huntsville who called her a dog on one of the message boards decided he would run by her and fling her skirt up to reveal her purty pink panties. Munchkin didnt take to kindly to that and ran after the punk. What was most impressive was seeing Munchkin track down this guy down wearing 6 inch platforms. She caught him by the hair and delivered a series of body blows and front kicks to  the punks mid section. As he knelt over trying to catch his breath, Team PCA member Mike Kessling walked up to him and freeped on him, knocking him unconscious.<br>
<br>
The Huntsville punk was last seen being carted out to a meat wagon, breathing with help from a ventilator. <br>
Matchup #3 <br>
<br>
Mike Belfatto VS John Rich<br>
<br>
This was a Florida thing going on here. John Rich is a well known player having a penchant for the confrontation during, before, and after games. Dont know if this is well deserved or not.<br>
<br>
Mike Belfatto is the exact opposite of this as he sits there fumbling with his cards saying I cant do anything as he drops down 7 Urak minions against your 4 unarmored weaponless companions.<br>
<br>
Turns out that Mike banged Johns girlfriend at a territorial over the summer and John was none to pleased. As he confronted Mike, Mike invoked his superpower and barfed in Johns face. John screaming for help was overcome by the acidic smell associated with Mikes barf and passed out, hitting himself in the throat on the way to the floor. <br>
<br>
<br>
Matchup #4 Tag team event. <br>
<br>
Team PCA vs The Huntsville gang<br>
<br>
There seems to be some rivalry between Atlanta and Huntsville. Both claim to have the best local tournament scene and the best tournament directors. Actually both are right, they are both excellent scenes with great TDs but hey, this is DCON where anything can happen and usually does. Clay Ramey and Effridge Englhart were paired up in a game early in the tournament and were seen yelling and screaming at each other over who was the actual creator of the white arrows mirror deck. They just couldnt seem to focus on the game itself and ended up decking each other and ran out of time at site 6 and all tiebreakers tied. It came down to a coin flip which Effridge lost. He then kicked Clay in the Jimmy but slipped on the floor in the process and hit his head on the table. Niether player could continue in the tournament. The rest of the Atlanta and Huntsville then engaged in a chair throwing match with members on all sides getting busted up.<br>
<br>
Gabe Alonso and Matt Lush, playing a game at a nearby table proceeded to beat the living tar out of all 23 members of Atlanta and Huntsville who were in attendance.<br>
<br>
 Matchup #5 <br>
<br>
The entire Lord of The Rings community versus the creator of Galadriels Mirror. HEY we found out who it was....after him!!!!! It turned out that it was Joe Alread after all despite numerous denials. Someone finally talked Bojo into telling everyone who it was. As the huge mob descended on Joe, Bojo yelled into the microphone, the Mirror is BANNED!!! This calmed the crowd down a lot and probably saved Joes life<br>
<br>
This in effect ended decipher con as all of the top players except for 2 were playing Mirror decks. The ones who weren&#39;t? Justin Abdullah Alderman and Bastian Winklehaus.<br>
<br>
Matchup #6 The final matchup <br>
<br>
We couldnt have this article without an actual game going on could we? <br>
<br>
Justin was playing When Hobbits Attack version 6.0 and has been playing this same exact deck since last January with a few new cards added in with each new set. <br>
<br>
Bastian was playing some sort of bastardized big fellowship with Nazgul minions.<br>
<br>
Justin won the bid by showing 2 to Bastians 1. Justin said I will play first. He revealed the Prancing Pony. Justin deployed Legolas,a hobbit sword on Merry, blade of Gondor on Boromir  and says, Ill walk. Bastian starts laughing out loud and saysohhhhh you are so focking stupid! You forgot to get Aragorn with Prancing Pony. He shows the Weatherhills and deploys Ulaire Attea with Morgul gates and then puts a Nazgul sword and a black steed on him. Justin says oh shyte under his breath but looks in his hand to find 2 stealths and hides from the big nasty Nazgul.<br>
<br>
Bastian gets Aragorn, deploys Gandalf, Elrond, Boromir, and Sam along with Aragorns sword giving Justin 27 twilight at site 2. Well Justin has the minion hand from hell of trolls keyward, cave troll, 2 Moria scouts, Enquea, and 3 scimitars. He deploys a scout for 2 and scimitar, draws a goblin armory, plays it. 25 left. Plays another scout and scimitar for 2, adds 1 draws a card, another armory, 24 left. Deploys Enquea for 7 and the other armory, 17 left. Deploys trolls keyward for 5 and a scimitar adding 2 back, draws a card, 14 left. Throws down Old Snarly for 12, and so 2 left in the pool.<br>
<br>
Maneuver- Bastian- I pass (I am screwed in German) Justin- Ill mow down Legolas with Enquea and Bastian says- I can do nothing.<br>
<br>
Archery- Bastian- I pass ( I am totally screwed in German) Justin- I pass<br>
<br>
Assignment- Cave troll on Sam, scouts on Gandalf and Boromir, Keyward on Aragorn, and Enquea on Gimli. They all take wounds and Sam dies horribly. Bastian, holding a stealth in his hand does not want to lose anyone else to the fierce Cave Troll so he assigns Frodo to the fierce skirmish.<br>
Bastian- I play Hobbit Stealth to cancel the battle. Justin says I will play Relentless to cancel the stealth event. Frodo is overwhelmed badly and so is Bastian making Abdullah the 2002 World Champion.<br>
<br>
Bastian says- Fock this game, I am going to play Star Wars!  <br>
<br>
And that ends Deciphercon 2002. Thank you for attending. Matt Lush, Neal, and I will be down the street at the titty bar as usual. If we can find one.<br>
 <br>
<br>
